body_html:
@coutner @xsr-ai dropout function uses the operation: RandomUniform, to ignore some of the weights.
As this operation has not been implemented for TFLite, it raises the flag of Unsupported TensorFlow op

When you remove the dropout function, the model does not use the RandomUniform operation. As a result of which the conversion completes successfully.

I hope that solves it.

body:
@coutner @xsr-ai `dropout` function uses the operation: `RandomUniform`, to ignore some of the weights. 
As this operation has not been implemented for TFLite, it raises the flag of `Unsupported TensorFlow op`

When you remove the dropout function, the model does not use the `RandomUniform` operation. As a result of which the conversion completes successfully. 

I hope that solves it.
